      <h1>Excel Pivot Tables & Charts</h1>
      <p class="tagline">
        Build a simple dashboard using <strong>your own dataset</strong> (grades, sales, survey, etc.).
      </p>
      <div class="layout-two-col" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
        <div>
          <h3>What you’ll learn</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>What PivotTables and PivotCharts are.</li>
            <li>How to summarize your data without formulas.</li>
            <li>How to add slicers (big filter buttons).</li>
            <li>How to arrange everything into a dashboard.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="box">
            <strong>Important:</strong> You can use <em>any</em> dataset that looks like a table:
            one row per record, one header per column.
          </div>
        </div>
