    <!-- Slide 2: Dataset -->
    <section class="slide">
      <h2>1. Your Dataset</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <p>You can use any table-like data. For example:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Student grades</li>
            <li>Sales transactions</li>
            <li>Survey responses</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Typical columns:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Date</strong> (when something happened)</li>
            <li><strong>Category</strong> (subject, product, question type…)</li>
            <li><strong>Amount / Score</strong> (numeric value to summarize)</li>
            <li><strong>Region / Group</strong> (class, campus, store, team…)</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="box-note">
            Make sure the first row has <strong>column names</strong> and there are no completely blank rows in the middle.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="image-frame">
            <!-- dataset table illustration -->
            <svg viewBox="0 0 260 150" aria-label="Example dataset table">
