    <!-- Slide 3: Table -->
    <section class="slide">
      <h2>2. Step 1 – Turn Data into an Excel Table</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <p>This makes the data easier to work with and keeps PivotTables connected.</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Click any cell inside your dataset.</li>
            <li>On the ribbon, click <span class="pill">Insert</span> → <span class="pill">Table</span>.</li>
            <li>Make sure <strong>“My table has headers”</strong> is checked.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
            <li>With the table selected, go to <span class="pill">Table Design</span> and give it a name (e.g., <code>MyData</code>).</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="box">
            <strong>Why?</strong> Tables automatically extend as you add rows, and PivotTables can refresh from them.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="image-frame">
            <!-- Insert Table illustration -->
            <svg viewBox="0 0 260 150" aria-label="Insert Table on ribbon">
              <title>Insert table from ribbon</title>
              <!-- ribbon -->
              <rect x="0" y="0" width="260" height="50" fill="#111827" />
              <text x="15" y="20" font-size="9" fill="#e5e7eb">Home</text>
              <text x="55" y="20" font-size="9" fill="#9ca3af">Insert</text>
              <text x="105" y="20" font-size="9" fill="#9ca3af">Page Layout</text>
              <!-- highlight Insert -->
              <rect x="48" y="22" width="40" height="3" fill="#2563eb"/>
              <!-- Table button area -->
              <rect x="10" y="55" width="80" height="30" rx="4" fill="#020617" stroke="#374151"/>
              <rect x="15" y="60" width="24" height="18" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="0.5"/>
              <text x="45" y="74" font-size="8" fill="#e5e7eb">Table</text>
              <!-- dataset preview below -->
              <rect x="110" y="55" width="140" height="75" rx="5" fill="#020617" stroke="#374151"/>
              <rect x="112" y="57" width="136" height="12" fill="#111827"/>
              <rect x="112" y="71" width="136" height="11" fill="#020617" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="0.4"/>
              <rect x="112" y="84" width="136" height="11" fill="#020617" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="0.4"/>
            </svg>
            <div class="image-caption">Click inside your data → Insert → Table → confirm “My table has headers”.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
