      <h2>6. Step 5 – Create a Second PivotTable</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <p>Dashboards usually have more than one view. Example:</p>
          <p><strong>“Amount per Region”</strong> or <strong>“Average Score per Group”</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Go back to the sheet with your table (<code>MyData</code>).</li>
            <li>Insert another PivotTable:
              <ul>
                <li>Click inside the table.</li>
                <li><span class="pill">Insert</span> → <span class="pill">PivotTable</span>.</li>
                <li>Use the same source table.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>In the new PivotTable, drag:
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Region / Group</strong> → <strong>Rows</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Amount / Score</strong> → <strong>Values</strong> (Sum or Average)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Add another PivotChart from this PivotTable and rename it (e.g., <em>Amount by Region</em>).</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="box">
