    <!-- Slide 8: Slicers -->
    <section class="slide">
      <h2>7. Step 6 – Add Slicers (Friendly Filters)</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <p><strong>Slicers</strong> are big buttons that filter PivotTables and charts.</p>
          <h3>Example slicers you can use</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Date</strong> (Year, Month)</li>
            <li><strong>Category</strong> (Subject, Product type)</li>
            <li><strong>Region / Group</strong> (Campus, Class, Store)</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>How to add a slicer</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Click on a PivotTable.</li>
            <li>Go to <span class="pill">PivotTable Analyze</span> → <span class="pill">Insert Slicer</span>.</li>
            <li>Check the field you want (e.g., <strong>Date</strong> or <strong>Category</strong>).</li>
            <li>Click <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="box-note">
            Try clicking different buttons in the slicer. Watch how the PivotTable and chart change.
          </div>
          <div class="box-warn">
            Right now, each slicer may only control <em>one</em> PivotTable. We’ll link them soon.
          </div>
        </div>
