      <h2>8. Step 7 – Create a Dashboard Sheet</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <h3>8.1 New sheet for the dashboard</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Click the <strong>+</strong> at the bottom of Excel to add a sheet.</li>
            <li>Right-click the sheet tab → <strong>Rename</strong> → type <strong>Dashboard</strong>.</li>
          </ol>
          <h3>8.2 Move charts and slicers</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Click a chart border → press <code>Ctrl + X</code> (Cut).</li>
            <li>Go to the <strong>Dashboard</strong> sheet → press <code>Ctrl + V</code> (Paste).</li>
            <li>Do the same for the second chart.</li>
            <li>Cut and paste the slicer(s) to the Dashboard sheet as well.</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="box">
            Arrange them so that slicers are on top or on the side, with charts underneath.
          </div>
