    <!-- Slide 10: Connect slicers -->
    <section class="slide">
      <h2>9. Step 8 – Connect Slicers to All PivotTables</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <p>Make one slicer control <strong>all</strong> charts (all PivotTables behind them).</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Click on a slicer (e.g., the Date slicer).</li>
            <li>On the ribbon, go to <span class="pill">Slicer</span> (Slicer Tools).</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Report Connections</strong> or <strong>PivotTable Connections</strong>.</li>
            <li>Tick every PivotTable that should respond to this slicer.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
          </ol>
          <p>Repeat for other slicers.</p>
          <div class="box">
            Now when you click a Year or Category:
            <ul>
              <li>All PivotTables update.</li>
              <li>All PivotCharts update.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
