    <section class="slide">
      <h2>10. Step 9 – Test & Reflect</h2>
      <div class="layout-two-col">
        <div>
          <div class="big-number">✓</div>
          <p>You’ve turned your own dataset into an interactive Excel dashboard.</p>
          <h3>Try this with your data</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Click a single <strong>Year</strong> or <strong>Category</strong> in the slicer.</li>
            <li>Try selecting multiple items (hold <code>Ctrl</code> while clicking).</li>
            <li>Observe which bars go up or down in the charts.</li>
            <li>Use the clear filter icon on the slicer to reset.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Quick mapping guide</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Category</strong> → Subject, Product, Question type, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Amount</strong> → Score, Sales, Quantity, Time spent, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Region/Group</strong> → Class, Campus, Store, Team, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Date</strong> → Exam date, Sale date, Submission date, etc.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="box-note">
            Once comfortable, students can add:
            <ul>
              <li>Top 10 categories by Amount.</li>
              <li>Average score per student or per class.</li>
              <li>Response counts per survey option.</li>
            </ul>
